text: What is the best SNMP implementation for Python?
I'm doing some GUI prototyping with Python for an SNMP application.
Looking around there seem to be a number of python libraries I could use.
As I'm prototyping I value a nice clean easy API over speed and preferably a commonly packaged library.
Obviously the package should be open source.
So far I've been looking PySNMP, Twisted-Snmp, pynetsnmp and seafelt's libsnmp.
